cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "tokenfit: heuristic token-count estimation for LLM context windows"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2025-05-05"
license: MIT
url: "https://github.com/vdeshmukh203/tokenfit"
repository-code: "https://github.com/vdeshmukh203/tokenfit"
keywords:
  - large language models
  - token estimation
  - context window
  - natural language processing
  - Python
authors:
  - family-names: Deshmukh
    given-names: Vaibhav
abstract: >
  tokenfit is a lightweight, dependency-free Python library that estimates
  how many tokens a text or chat conversation will consume for a given large
  language model (LLM). It uses pre-calibrated character-to-token ratios per
  model family to produce conservative, rounded-up estimates entirely offline
  and without any API calls. The library supports GPT-3.5, GPT-4, GPT-4-Turbo,
  GPT-4o, the Claude 3 and 3.5 families, and the Gemini family. A Tkinter
  desktop GUI is included for interactive exploration.
